div.div: Made in Abyss: Retsujitsu no Ougonkyou
Adventure, Drama, Fantasy, Horror, Mystery, Sci-Fi

The second season of Made in Abyss. Directly after the events of Made in Abyss: Fukaki Tamashii no Reimei, the third installment of Made in Abyss covers the adventures of Reg, Riko, and Nanachi in the Sixth Layer, The Capital of the Unreturned. Note: The last episode aired with a runtime of ~48 minutes as opposed to the standard 24 minute long episode.
Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka IV: Shin Shou Meikyuu-hen

The fourth season of Dungeon ni Deai wo Motomeru no wa Machigatteiru Darou ka. Intrepid adventurer Bell Cranel has leveled up, but he can’t rest on his dungeoneering laurels just yet. The Hestia Familia still has a long way to go before it can stand toe-to-toe with the other Familias of Orario — but before Bell can set out on his next mission, reports of a brutal murder rock the adventuring community! One of Bell’s trusted allies stands accused of the horrible crime, and it’s up to Bell and his friends to clear their name and uncover a nefarious plot brewing in the dungeon’s dark depths. (Source: Sentai Filmworks)

Sequel to Tenkuu Shinpan. This series follows a different cast of characters and explores new areas. Senya is just an ordinary guy, who wanted to become an astronaut as a kid. One day and suddenly, he's transported into another world after seeing on the rooftop of his school something like a "tower" going across the sky. There, he witnesses a ruined world, where skyscrapers are connected by suspension bridges. Senya, perplexed, manages to see a girl standing on the roof of another building, as well as a masked man holding a bloody weapon in his hands... (Source: Japanese publisher, translated)
Akuyaku Reijou desu ga, Shiawase ni Natte Misemasu wa!

Annuled engagements, "serves you right"s, condemnation events, doting, royalty, reincarnated heroines, banishment endings... it's fully loaded with all the charms of villainesses!! Despite all the Villainess' stories starting off in dire straits, in the end they're...all happy endings♪ A comicalization of popular villainess stories that were published on Shousetsuka ni Narou! An anthology of oneshots with happy endings!! Volume 1 Cover illustration: Maro 1. "The Villainess Will Obtain True Love" by Hoshino Soumei Author: Nekomata Doremi An annulled engagement at a graduation party?! 2. "The Tale of the Noble Girl who will go to a Monastery after her Engagement Annulment" by Sorakura SHIJIKI, Author: Yuuki Satoru Banishment after her younger sister steals her fiance?! 3. "I Will Definitely Get My Engagement Annulled! ~I will become a Villainess!" by Kuroe Yui, Author: Reiga Utsuho To break off her engagement, she harasses the daughter of a Baron?! 4. "Shall We Walk Hand in Hand Down the Flowery Path of Evil?" by Yamashiro Umeta, Author: Mafuyubi After her engagement is annulled, she gets married to a fat old baldy?! 5. "The Villainess Trifles with the Second Prince's First Love" by Oshitsuji Ei, Author: Mizuno Saaya After being condemned, the second prince appears before me... Volume 2 Cover illustration: Maro 1. "It's Been 10 Years Since You Asked to Break Off Our Engagement, If You Insist That Much, Let's Break It Off!" by Maro, Author: Yoshimura She's been told multiple times since they were young to break off the engagement?! 2. "The Villainess Laughs Innocently" by Oshitsuji Ei, Author: Yoruru A Condemnation Event after being called out to the rear garden?! 3. div.span: Turbulent Adventurers are Introverted, Observant, Feeling, Prospecting and Turbulent. Adventurers are flexible and charming, always ready to explore and experience something new. They tend to have open minds, approaching life, new experiences, and people with grounded warmth.
Likely prefers fewer, yet deep and meaningful, social interactions and feels drawn to calmer environments.
Likely pragmatic and down-to-earth, with a strong focus on what is happening or very likely to happen.
Likely values emotional expression and sensitivity, prioritizing empathy, social harmony, and cooperation.
Likely very good at improvising and adapting. Tends to be flexible and values novelty above stability.
Likely self-conscious, sensitive to stress, success-driven, perfectionistic, and eager to improve.
